text: <@U2Q5LPHGS> pinned a message to this channel.
<@U25PYL3Q8> If I’m forced to work in Wordpress, I ALWAYS go with the DIVI Theme by Elegant Themes. Solid, supported, easy to design.
I've heard a lot about DIVI on reddit. seems a lot of people like that. <@U25C6PU56>
Elegant Themes has been around for a long time. It’s about as safe as you can get with out-of-the-box theming in Wordpress IMHO <@U25PYL3Q8>
I do not like DIVI for all of the extra crap that it includes. It is a drag and drop editor tho. I prefer to use Timber

<@U4RP6AGV9> commented on <@U25C65C3S>’s file <https://HubSpotdev.slack.com/files/U25C65C3S/F7TN2P0MT/-.py|https://HubSpotdev.slack.com/files/U25C65C3S/F7TN2P0MT/-.py>: Don't forget the ".change()" or .trigger('change') if you're modifying an embedded form
